headline.main: FRENCH LINE YIELDS; American Air and Tank Forces Launch Swift Counter-Assault ENEMY FORCE IS STRONG U.S. Bombers Range From Gabes to Bizerte Area in Raids on Foe's Communications AXIS MAKES AN ADVANCE IN ATTACK IN TUNISIA FRENCH LINE YIELDS IN CENTRAL TUNISIA

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, Jan. 31 -- German tanks, infantry and artillery brushed aside a small French force defending Faid Pass, on the road between Sfax and Sbeitla in Central Tunisia, yesterday and advanced about six and a half miles beyond the pass.
abstract: Ger tanks break through French lines defending Faid Pass; US air power attempts to stem Gers; US tanks aid; Gers continue advance; move seen as effort to protect Rommel flank; Messina, Sicily, raided
